<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-9625] Unable to Describe broker configurations that have been set via IncrementalAlterConfigs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9625</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There seem to be at least two bugs in the broker configuration APIs and/or logic:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Broker throttles are incorrectly marked as sensitive configurations.  This includes leader.replication.throttled.rate, follower.replication.throttled.rate, replica.alter.log.dirs.io.max.bytes.per.second.  This means that their values cannot be read back by DescribeConfigs after they are set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. When we clear the broker throttles via incrementalAlterConfigs, DescribeConfigs continues returning the old throttles indefinitely.  In other words, the clearing is not reflected in the Describe API.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
